title: Search ends for Navy SEALs lost at sea on mission to seize Iranian arms
description: After an exhaustive search scouring 21,000 square miles off the coast of Somalia, two Navy SEALs reported missing during the boarding of a ship carrying Iranian weapons to Houthi fighters were declared dead by the Pentagon.

title: Shelling in eastern Ukraine kills 27, Russian-backed authorities say
description: Officials in the city of Donetsk said the shells landed in a busy shopping area and blamed the strikes on Ukraine’s military.

title: Iranian-linked militants strike Iraqi base housing U.S. troops
description: The attack against Ain al-Asad Air Base injured at least one Iraqi service member, Centcom said. Some U.S. personnel were evaluated for traumatic brain injuries.

title: Israel-Gaza war live updates: U.S. prepares for sustained military campaign against Houthis in Yemen
description: In Iraq, a number of U.S. troops are being evaluated for traumatic brain injuries after other Iran-backed militants attacked an air base there, U.S. Central Command said.

title: War in Gaza is making childbirth a nightmare
description: Doctors and aid workers say infant and maternity mortality have spiked.
